Why I, an avid gun owner, hate Red Jacket Firearms
data.description:
Their show is rather obviously staged. I find it extremely unlikely a black man in a business suit with a continental accent will come to Generic Redneck Gun Shop, Louisiana to buy four MG-42's on a quad mount (but only because buying four M2 .50-caliber machineguns would be too pricy!)

Many featured things on the show (such as their double M16's) were not even constructed by them - it was outsourced to a far more respectable machine shop called Tromix.

They are all ego and act like complete assholes. In one show, they were apparently busy with a build and decided to shrug off a couple looking for a home defense gun by selling them a cheap .22 pistol. Not smart.

They do messy cut-jobs, and most of their abominations are downright dangerous. When guns just explode on them they act surprised for some reason...

The guns they sell commercially under their name are just AK parts kits assembled on US-made receivers, something you could literally do in your kitchen.

Rather than talking an elderly woman out of buying a Desert Eagle in .50 AE, they instead put a shoulder stock on it and give her a paperwork-ridden SBR, which is simply fucking stupid.﻿

In one scene where the daughter was supposed to be "test-firing" the Desert Eagle, they sneakily used a Beretta M9 (a far lower recoil firearm) in the actual firing scene, as if nobody would notice.

They got into legal trouble over some really stupid decisions they made.

But the VERY worst of all, they chop up rare and historical NFA firearms for their "customers" (which are clearly actors) which cannot be repaired nor replaced - when you fuck up that WWII-era machinegun, its fucked up forever, and now the next generation cannot enjoy that piece of history, because you stupid-ass rednecks decided it would be better spraypainted red and chopped up with a hacksaw. Disgusting.
